The paper deals with the hard core model in statistical physics, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of computer science and physics. The paper specifically focuses on the phenomenon of strong spatial mixing and its connection to the connective constant of a graph. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.GT (Discrete Mathematics), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
